In anticipation of Fall Phase 1 enrollments appointments starting on 4/18, I want to share what I can with the understanding that a more complete statement will be made later by EECS/campus leadership.
Here's what is known:
  • CompSci classes will be open for enrollment when phase 1 enrollment appointments start.
  • Some changes have been made to the CompSci enrollment policies that are not related to funding or enrollment capacities and you can view the updated policies at Getting Into Computer Science Classes webpage. This page isn't public yet but you can view it here for now.)

Key changes include:

  • Undergraduate students interested in taking graduate CompSci classes will now have to wait until after August 1st to obtain permission codes to enroll. This change provides graduate students the best chance to enroll before undergrads take seats in classes.
  • Data Science majors and declared EECS/EIS/LSCS minors will now be limited to a limited list of upper division CompSci classes in which they can enroll/waitlist. You can see the CLASS NOTES for each class for more information.
I anticipate being able to make the CompSci classes visible on CalCentral by 10pm on Saturday, April 16th. Whenever classes are made visible, you can expect that all classes will be made visible around the same time and I will post an update here. If I am unable to make that deadline, I will also post an update here.
EECS leadership, faculty, and staff understand that you may have questions regarding some of the changes you see in the enrollment policies and on CalCentral but, unfortunately, we will be unable to provide any more information at this time. 
Finally, I have been asked to share that leadership is committed to providing access to classes needed to declare the L&S Computer Science major and anticipates that all current and newly-admitted students interested in the major will be accommodated consistent with current EECS policies. ( I cannot clarify this statement as I am only sharing the information on someone else's behalf.)
Thank you for your continued patience!
Cindy Conners
CompSci Enrollment Manager
